Rihanna just became the first female artiste to reach two billion streams on Apple Music. She continues to be the groundbreaking, record shattering superstar that we know and love her for. The bad gal keeps on winning as Apple announced that she became the first female artiste to cross two billion streams worldwide, making an already special International Women’s Day that much sweeter. As Apple Music dropped a list of the 20 most streamed women in music for IWD via Instagram, the ‘bad girl’ reigned supreme, landing the number one spot over star-studded names such as Taylor Swift, who came in second, Beyoncé (third), and Adele (fifth).